Orlando Pirates coach Josef Zinnbauer. JOHANNESBURG - Orlando Pirates coach Josef Zinnbauer is leaving the club. Pirates has granted the head coach leave to go home to Germany. The club said Zinnbauer's son has been admitted to hospital. "Unfortunately, out of respect for Mr Zinnbauer and his family we cannot divulge anything more except to say that his son is in hospital," Pirates said in a statement.
"The coach has requested for his family’s privacy to be respected during this difficult time." The 50-year-old is expected to return to the club soon though it's not clear when. Zinnbauer leaves at the back of an emphatic win against arch-rivals Kaizer Chiefs. Pirates beat Chiefs 3-0 in the MTN 8 semi-final first leg.